# Document 05 — Backend Schema

Define data structure before migrations or API routes.

## Required sections

- All tables: columns, types, PKs, FKs
- Indexes for fast lookup columns
- Auth model and provider
- Row Level Security rules
- User roles and permissions
- Sensitive fields (encryption or external storage)
- File/media storage paths
- Webhooks or event triggers (optional)
- API endpoint list (optional)

## Agent rules

- Write migrations from this schema — do not invent tables at runtime.
- Every user-owned row must have RLS aligned with the doc.
- Payment and secrets live in third-party services, not plain DB columns.
